# Build context is this project root (the ale-kasm Dockerfile is built with
# `docker build -f ale_run/environments/images/ale_kasm/Dockerfile . ` from
# here so it can COPY ale_run/agents/_assets/cua_mcp_server/). Everything the
# image needs is COPYd by explicit path; this file keeps the context lean by
# excluding the large dirs the daemon would otherwise tar up and send.
#
# Patterns are relative to the context root. The cua MCP bridge source lives at
# ale_run/agents/_assets/cua_mcp_server/{src,package*.json} — none of the
# patterns below match it (it is not under upstream/ or node_modules/), so it
# is preserved for the COPY at Dockerfile line 96.

# Virtualenvs / VCS / logs — never needed in an image.
**/.venv/
.venv/
**/.git/
.git/
**/.logs/
.logs/

# Vendored upstream agent source trees (forks cloned at runtime, not baked).
**/upstream/

# Node + Python build artifacts (node_modules is rebuilt on-substrate by
# ensure_cua_mcp_server; never ship it into the context).
**/node_modules/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc

# Editor / OS cruft.
**/.DS_Store
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/
